            "subject": "LU-0000 tests: llapi EC partial, mirror-id, parity stripe size"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-08-11 20:13:19.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-09-04 23:39:46.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-0000 utils: allow mirror rw of mirror 0",
        "message": "LU-0000 utils: allow mirror rw of mirror 0\n\nEC will require specifying designated IO to direct IO to\nthe parity components.  The easiest way to do this for\nnon-mirrored files is to allow using mirror read/write to\nmirror ID 0.\n\nNB:\nThe read implementation is fine, but the write\nimplementation changes the lease type from RESYNC to a\nplain lease - this is incorrect, since we'll want EC\ncomp write to be a resync just like a normal mirror\nwrite.\n\nThis requires fixing up some of the layout implementation\nfirst.\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\nTest-Parameters: forjanitoronly\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I5d6499526f02e72b4fe0ed95d596226769e6b488\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
